Package: foofactors
Title: Handy tools for working with factors
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: person("Stephen", "Chignell", role=c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "stephen.chignell@alumni.ubc.ca")
Description: Factors have driven people to extreme measures, like ordering
    custom conference ribbons and laptop stickers to express how HELLNO we
    feel about stringsAsFactors. And yet, sometimes you need them. Can they
    be made less maddening? Let's find out. NOTE: this package builds off 
	of the original foofactors package developed by Jenny Bryan, and is for
    pedagogical purposes only.	
Depends:
    R (>= 3.2.2)
License: MIT + file LICENSE
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.1.0
Suggests: testthat,
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
Imports: 
    dplyr,
    stringr
VignetteBuilder: knitr
URL: https://github.com/schignel/foofactors
BugReports: https://github.com/schignel/foofactors/issues
